<Layout title="Information">
  <div class="info-page">

    <!-- Bio: Chinese first, then English -->
    <div class="info-bio-stacked">
      <div class="info-bio-stacked__zh">
        <p>
          沈庭華，1997，台北藝術大學美術學系碩士，以平面繪畫、版畫、陶塑等為主要創作媒材，
          取材大多於生活與自然的觀察，透過細微的感知將這些媒材加以闡述及想像，
          將細碎的感受擴增至作品之中，題材擴及植物、地質、水文等面向，
          探索社會中人造物之介入狀態，回應人造物及自然產物間的矛盾關係，
          透過個人的感知經驗與材質觀察，試圖紀錄與保留即將消逝的事物。
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-bio-stacked__en">
        <p>
          Shen, Ting-Hua (b. 1997, Taipei, Taiwan) works across ceramics, glass, and mixed media
          to explore the transformation of natural materials and their relation to geological and
          oceanic phenomena. Her practice draws from subtle observations of drifting, solidifying,
          and regeneration, translating temporal and spatial experiences into material forms.
        </p>
        <p>
          In 2025, Shen presented her solo exhibition <em>Colors from the Flames</em> at ISland
          Art Space, Taipei, which continued her investigation into the alchemical transformation
          of materials through fire. The previous year, her exhibition <em>Gathering the Distance</em>
          at the same venue extended her research on volcanic pumice and drifting matter, exploring
          how geological and oceanic movements connect distant landscapes and bodily experiences.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

